@node Over "Overview"

@{b}OVERVIEW------------------------------------------------------------------@{ub}

This is an implementation of the Tunnels & Trolls game (5th Edition), in
its solitaire form, consisting of the game engine and 25 adventures. It
allows you to play the adventures without pen, paper, dice, cards, nor the
adventures themselves. The complete T&T rulebook will prove handy but is
not essential.
  The included adventures are:

    * Abyss (1980)
    * Amulet of the Salkti (1984)
    * Arena of Khazan (1979)
    * Beyond the Silvered Pane (1978)
    * Blue Frog Tavern (1981)
    * Buffalo Castle (1976)
    * Captif d'Yvoire (1984)
    * Caravan to Tiern (1989)
    * Circle of Ice (1980)
    * City of Terrors (1978)
    * Dargon's Dungeon (1977)
    * Deathtrap Equalizer (1977)
    * Gamesmen of Kasar (1982)
    * Goblin Lake (1979)
    * Labyrinth (1977)
    * Mistywood (1981)
    * Naked Doom (1977)
    * Overkill (1977)
    * Red Circle (1987)
    * Sea of Mystery (1981)
    * Sewers of Oblivion (1980)
    * Sorcerer Solitaire (1979)
    * Sword for Hire (1979)
    * Trollstone Caverns (1979)
    * Weirdworld (1977)

In its current state, it is mostly complete. Notably, many special
combats, unique item powers, and spells are unimplemented. While playing,
most unimplemented text is shown in blue.
  The basis for this conversion is the Corgi edition of the T&T 5th
Edition rules, although the Flying Buffalo editions have also been
consulted.
  These Amiga version features are not present in the Windows version:

    * graphics; and
    * ReAction-based character sheet.
@endnode

@node Requ "System Requirements"

@{b}SYSTEM REQUIREMENTS-------------------------------------------------------@{ub}

These are for the AmigaOS 2.x version of T&T:

@{b}Hardware@{ub}         Required        about 4Mb free RAM
@{b}Firmware@{ub}         Required        Kickstart 2.0+
@{b}Software@{ub}         Required        AmigaOS 2.0+
                 Recommended     AmigaOS 3.5+

The Amiga version, when running under OS3.5+, features a ReAction-based
auto-updating character sheet, and graphics corresponding to the
illustrations in the original adventures.
  The Windows version should work on Windows 95 or later. However, you
won't get the text colours under Win95/98/ME; it is recommended to use
WinNT/2K/XP/Vista/7/8.
  Windows XP: If you are getting the wrong glyphs (eg. for the "half" (˝)
symbol), click the system menu of the console window, choose the
"Properties" menu item, choose the "Font" tab, choose "Raster Fonts",
then click "OK". When asked, choose "Save properties for future windows
with same title" and click "OK".
  A similar procedure will likely work for other versions of Windows.
@endnode

@node Usag "Usage"

@{b}USAGE---------------------------------------------------------------------@{ub}

@{b}CLI Arguments@{ub}

                                    @{b}TnT@{ub}

@{b}Format:    TnT@{ub} [<filename>]

@{b}Purpose:@{ub}   An implementation of Tunnels and Trolls.

@{b}Specification:@{ub}

    file:  the name of a character to load at startup.
@endnode

@node Cred "Credits and Licence"

@{b}CREDITS AND LICENCE-------------------------------------------------------@{ub}

@{b}Credits@{ub}

This implementation of Tunnels & Trolls was designed and programmed by
James Jacobs of Amigan Software. The game itself was designed by Ken St.
Andre. The included adventures were written by various people, and
illustrated by Josh Kirby (Corgi) and various other people (Flying
Buffalo). The game and adventures were published by Flying Buffalo (all)
and Corgi Books (AK/AS/BF/BS/CD/CT/DE/GK/MW/ND/RB/SH/TC).

@{b}EMail:@{ub}                  amigansoftware\@gmail.com

@{b}Amiga Developer Number:@{ub} AD874

@{b}Website:@{ub}                http://amigan.1emu.net/releases/

